{# ── SHORT VERSION · TL;DR prose — the honest meta-answer in one paragraph. #qb-support-tldr-body
     speakable id preserved. (H2) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-tldr" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Which &ldquo;support&rdquo; do you actually need?</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose"><p id="qb-support-tldr-body">{{ tldr | safe }}</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INTUIT'S REAL CHANNELS · r-3 dc-cards, one per product. HONESTY HARD LIMIT:
     channels are described GENERICALLY — NO phone number, NO hours, NO wait times, NO "24/7"
     anywhere; each card defers current specifics to Intuit's official support link. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qb-support-channels" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Intuit&rsquo;s real support channels</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">How to reach Intuit, by product.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:70ch;">These are the channels Intuit actually operates &mdash; in-product Help and the virtual assistant, the official QuickBooks support site and Community forums, and a contact/callback request flow. Desktop, Payroll, and Payments each have their own paths. <strong>We don&rsquo;t publish Intuit phone numbers, hours, or wait times here</strong> &mdash; those change, and fabricating them would be dishonest. For current specifics, go straight to <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit&rsquo;s official support</a>.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for c in channels %}
      <div class="dc-card">
        <h3>{{ c.product | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Channels:</strong> {{ c.what | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Can help with:</strong> {{ c.can | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Can&rsquo;t help with:</strong> {{ c.cant | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>How to escalate:</strong> {{ c.escalate | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── TRIAGE · the load-bearing honest split (Sheet-7 rule 6). r-2 of two checklists in dc-card:
     Contact Intuit for… vs. Talk to an independent ProAdvisor for… ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-triage">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Where your issue belongs</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Intuit, or an independent ProAdvisor?</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:70ch;">The fastest way to the right help is to know which bucket your problem falls in. Anything touching your Intuit account goes to Intuit; anything inside your books comes to an independent firm.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      <div class="dc-card">
        <h3>Contact Intuit for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">
          {%- for t in triageIntuit %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p style="margin:16px 0 0;"><a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-accent);">Go to Intuit support &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="dc-card">
        <h3>Talk to an independent ProAdvisor for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">
          {%- for t in triageProAdvisor %}<li>{{ t | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p style="margin:16px 0 0;"><a href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review" style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:var(--color-accent);">Get the free file review &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── THE INDEPENDENT PATH · r-3 dc-cards — the three honest reasons to bring it to a firm. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qb-support-independent" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The independent path</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">When it&rsquo;s the books, not the software.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:70ch;">No software support line can fix accounting that&rsquo;s wrong inside your file. That&rsquo;s what an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm does &mdash; on a fixed fee, scoped in writing.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for p in independentPath %}
      <div class="dc-card">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ p.signal | safe }}</span>
        <h3>{{ p.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;"><strong>Honest scope:</strong> {{ p.honest | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CALM PHONE CTA · calm dc-card. Phone label is ALWAYS "Talk to a Certified ProAdvisor
     (independent firm)" (Sheet-7 rule 4) — never "QuickBooks support line". btn-cta + data-ga. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-call">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="dc-card" style="text-align:center;">
      <p class="call-breakout__title" style="font-weight:600;margin:0 0 8px;">Need help with the accounting inside your file?</p>
      <p class="call-breakout__sub prose" style="font-size:14.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:0 auto 18px;max-width:64ch;">A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor at TechBrot reviews your situation &mdash; a broken file, a cleanup, a setup or migration, payroll-in-file. The file review and discovery call are free; a written fixed-fee scope follows within 3 business days. {{ site.phone.display }} &middot; independent firm, not Intuit. For an Intuit account, billing, or login issue, <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">contact Intuit directly</a>.</p>
      <a class="btn btn-cta" href="tel:{{ site.phone.e164 }}" data-ga="phone_click" data-tb-event="phone_click" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;height:48px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:11px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Talk to a Certified ProAdvisor (independent firm)</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PAGE REVIEW · firm-level (founder-name-zero). David survives only as reviewedBy @id in
     schema. ── #}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="qb-support-review" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Page review &amp; standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:20px;">Honest-routing standards.</h2>
    <div class="prose-byline">
      <span class="prose-byline__mark"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 64 64" fill="#FCFBF8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M8 10 H38 V54 H26 V22 H8 Z"/><rect x="42" y="10" width="14" height="12"/></svg></span>
      <div><p class="prose-byline__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p><p class="prose-byline__meta">TechBrot &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:22px;">
      <p>This guide is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot</strong>, an independent ProAdvisor firm. We deliberately describe Intuit&rsquo;s support channels generically and do not publish Intuit phone numbers, hours, wait times, or &ldquo;24/7&rdquo; claims &mdash; those change, and stating them would mislead; for current specifics we link to <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit&rsquo;s official support</a>. TechBrot is an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by <a href="https://www.intuit.com/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit Inc.</a>; it provides no Intuit account, billing, subscription, login, or QuickBooks product support, and does not file tax returns or represent clients before the IRS. QuickBooks and Intuit are registered trademarks of Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-18</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-18</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-18 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · r-2 dc-cards. The Intuit support card is the canonical redirect for
     account/billing/login/subscription intent (Sheet-7 rule 6). ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-support-related">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Related</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Where to go next.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>
        <h3>{{ r.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <span class="hub-card__go">{{ r.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span>
      </a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
